Interface SnomedRefSetMember

  • All Superinterfaces:

    public interface SnomedRefSetMember
extends org.eclipse.emf.cdo.CDOObject
    Base representation of a SNOMED CT reference set member.

    The following features are supported:

    • Referenced Component Type
    • Effective Time
    • Active
    • Ref Set
    • Released
    • Referenced Component Id
    • Module Id
    • Ref Set Identifier Id

    See Also:
    SnomedRefSetPackage.getSnomedRefSetMember()

      • getEffectiveTime

        java.util.Date getEffectiveTime()
        Returns with the nominal date of release of the current reference set member. Could be null. If null the component has not been published yet, or may have unpublished changes.
        Returns:
        the value of the publication date. Could be null.

      • isSetEffectiveTime

        boolean isSetEffectiveTime()
        Returns true if the component has been published. In other words the reference set has a *NON* null effective time.
        More formally: 
         null != getEffectiveTime()
 
        

        

        Returns:
        

        whether the value of the 'Effective Time' attribute is set.

        isActive
        

        boolean isActive()
        

        Returns wit the status of the SNOMED CT reference set member.
 
        If the reference set member is active this will return with true, if the reference set member is retired 
 this method will return with false.
        

        

        Returns:
        

        true if the reference set member is active, otherwise it returns with false.
